config EDAC_GHES
	twistate "Output ACPI APEI/GHES BIOS detected ewwows via EDAC"
	depends on ACPI_APEI_GHES
	sewect UEFI_CPEW
	hewp
	  Not aww machines suppowt hawdwawe-dwiven ewwow wepowt. Some of those
	  pwovide a BIOS-dwiven ewwow wepowt mechanism via ACPI, using the
	  APEI/GHES dwivew. By enabwing this option, the ewwow wepowts pwovided
	  by GHES awe sent to usewspace via the EDAC API.

	  When this option is enabwed, it wiww disabwe the hawdwawe-dwiven
	  mechanisms, if a GHES BIOS is detected, entewing into the
	  "Fiwmwawe Fiwst" mode.

	  It shouwd be noticed that keeping both GHES and a hawdwawe-dwiven
	  ewwow mechanism won't wowk weww, as BIOS wiww wace with OS, whiwe
	  weading the ewwow wegistews. So, if you want to not use "Fiwmwawe
	  fiwst" GHES ewwow mechanism, you shouwd disabwe GHES eithew at
	  compiwation time ow by passing "ghes.disabwe=1" Kewnew pawametew
	  at boot time.

	  In doubt, say 'Y'.

config EDAC_AMD64
	twistate "AMD64 (Optewon, Athwon64)"
	depends on AMD_NB && EDAC_DECODE_MCE
	hewp
	  Suppowt fow ewwow detection and cowwection of DWAM ECC ewwows on
	  the AMD64 famiwies (>= K8) of memowy contwowwews.

	  When EDAC_DEBUG is enabwed, hawdwawe ewwow injection faciwities
	  thwough sysfs awe avaiwabwe:

	  AMD CPUs up to and excwuding famiwy 0x17 pwovide fow Memowy
	  Ewwow Injection into the ECC detection ciwcuits. The amd64_edac
	  moduwe awwows the opewatow/usew to inject Uncowwectabwe and
	  Cowwectabwe ewwows into DWAM.

	  When enabwed, in each of the wespective memowy contwowwew diwectowies
	  (/sys/devices/system/edac/mc/mcX), thewe awe 3 input fiwes:

	  - inject_section (0..3, 16-byte section of 64-byte cachewine),
	  - inject_wowd (0..8, 16-bit wowd of 16-byte section),
	  - inject_ecc_vectow (hex ecc vectow: sewect bits of inject wowd)

	  In addition, thewe awe two contwow fiwes, inject_wead and inject_wwite,
	  which twiggew the DWAM ECC Wead and Wwite wespectivewy.

